title.narrative: Execution rate of the activities under the responsibility of the Project in the strategic HR plan
Share of statistical output available to users through the open data portal
Number of knowledge products on economic development issues produced with NSS data and disseminated to large audiences
Number of outreach thematic activities to key stakeholders such as media, politicians, policy makers and academia
Share of sectorial statistical agencies that produce statistical information endorsed as official statistics by the INS
The new INS-CASP complex is furnished, has a data center, computers and operational internet links
A functional web-based data portal enabling access to the NSS data is developed and deployed
Institutional capacity assessment is completed for INS staff and 14 identified DEPs
African chart of statistics and code of conduct are disseminated widely to the public.
Annual budgeted work plan of the PIU is reviewed by the steering committee and submitted to the World Bank for no objection
The Project Steering Committee meets semi-annually to assess project performance, intermediate results and outcomes
The results based monitoring framework of the projet is defined, updated and validated by the Project Steering Committee
Operational M&E workshops with INS and all beneficiaries of the project are organized 3 times a year to assess the progress of planned activities
The PIU makes biannual progress reports available to the Project Steering Committee
Share of statistical products completed and published by the INS following international standards.
Number of annual reports on the implementation of the ESMF and the RPF produced and discussed in the Project Steering Committee
Annual growth rate of the number of hits on INS website
Number of trained students that pass the exam to get into regional statistics schools, with at least 10% women
Number of NSS staff with formal degree in statistics, informatics or demography
The INS-CASP complex is built and operational
